<% @current_tab = :Home %>
<% content_for :head do %>
	<%= stylesheet_link_tag('home') %>
	<%= javascript_include_tag('home') %>
<% end %>
<div id="main_content" class="login">
	<div class="content_bar" id="top">
		<div class="content">
			<h4>Welcome to the Nourishing Destiny Community</h4>
			<p>Take a moment to look around, and when you&rsquo;re ready, come take a course, check out the new articles, respond to a discussion, or meet fellow site members.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	<ul class="section_list">
		<li class="library">
			<h4><span>Browse Library</span></h4>
			<p>The library contains articles, audio, and video teachings by the most innovative practitioners and authors in the field of Chinese medicine. The library will continue to grow. Much of this content is free to registered users. <%= link_to "Go to Library", articles_url, :class => "more" %><span class="arrow">&nbsp;</span></p>
		</li>
		<li class="courses">
			<h4><span>Join Courses</span></h4>
			<p>Online courses are certified by the NCCAOM! These include PDA courses by many of the most highly regarded teachers in the field of Chinese medicine. Here we offer a new and engaging format for continuing education. <%= link_to "Go to Courses", courses_url, :class => "more" %><span class="arrow">&nbsp;</span></p>
		</li>
		<li class="discussions">
			<h4><span>Join Discussions</span></h4>
			<p>Start conversations in organized themes, and respond to the posts of both fellow practitioners, and community experts. Part blog, part forum, the Nourishing Destiny discussion area gives you the benefit of collective wisdom and a focused inquiry. <%= link_to "Go to Discussions", discussions_url, :class => "more" %><span class="arrow">&nbsp;</span></p>
		</li>
		<li class="people">
			<h4><span>Meet People</span></h4>
			<p>Members can create profiles and safely network with each other. Search the member database by interests, names, locations, or any key word. The membership database will grow to serve as a great referral source and as a dynamic way to meet practitioners with similar interests. <%= link_to "Go to People", users_url, :class => "more" %><span class="arrow">&nbsp;</span></p>
		</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<div id="sidebar">
</div>